A 62-year-old man was killed and three others sustained gunshot wounds when four suspects opened fire on them during a stokvel meeting in Umbumbulu, last week.Provincial police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said, “On 3 December at Thenjane Reserve in Umbumbulu, a group of stokvel members were at a house to divide stokvel money. While they were busy counting the money, four armed suspects entered. “They fired shots at the stokvel members and struck four members. The suspects fled the scene with a large sum of cash. The injured victims were taken to hospital for medical attention where a 62-year-old man later died. Charges of robbery and murder were opened for investigation at Umbumbulu SAPS.” “Members of the public are being warned not carrying and keep large amounts of cash in their homes. “Citizens should consider options that are lower risk like to carry as little cash as possible and consider making use of cellphone banking and internet transfers to pay accounts or ATMs to do the banking. “The bank accounts must be opened and transfers be done at a bank to avoid robberies,” added Mbele.